How can we trust those who were elected to represent the diverse & complicated communities when we now know their true thoughts & minds? They cannot represent communities when they despise the individuals that make up that community.

We expect more from our leaders- not just at the pulpit-when the cameras are rolling, but also behind closed doors. The abhorrent comments made by @kdeleon @cd6nury @gilcedillo Martinez @RonHerrera_396 are a true betrayal of those standards. They need to resign immediately.

No apology can make right the appalling, racist & dangerous rhetoric of what I heard on those recordings. The black civil rights movement became the blue print & cornerstone for most, if not all, civil rights movements for ALL marginalized communities in this country & worldwide.

My grandparents used to say, no matter how u slice an orange, what comes out is what's inside! The same can be said for Martinez, KDL & Herrera. African Americans continue to be thrown over the bridge that we built. We need true allies!
